**Course Reflection**

What were your initial expectations for the course? Did the course meet, exceed, or fall short of these expectations?

|- I expected SYSADM1 to provide a strong foundation in system administration, especially with practical tools and processes relevant to real-world scenarios. The course not only met my expectations but exceeded them by offering hands-on activities such as configuring DNS and DHCP using dnsmasq and incorporating multi-factor authentication into SOPs. These tasks deepened my understanding and made the learning experience highly engaging.|
| :- |

What were the main topics or concepts covered in the course? How did these topics contribute to your understanding of the subject matter?

|- For me, the standout topics were DNS and DHCP configuration, web server monitoring, and security policies like the ISSP. Configuring DNS and DHCP solidified my understanding of networking fundamentals, while web server monitoring taught me to analyze metrics like error rates and response times. Developing an ISSP gave me insights into creating comprehensive and enforceable policies, which is crucial for real-world IT management.|
| :- |

Reflecting on your learning process, what were the most effective strategies or techniques that helped you grasp and retain the course material?

|- Hands-on activities were the most effective for me, especially tasks like setting up dnsmasq and troubleshooting server issues. Breaking down complex tasks into smaller steps and collaborating with classmates allowed me to internalize the concepts better. Documenting my processes also helped reinforce what I learned.|
| :- |

Were there any particular assignments, projects, or activities that significantly enhanced your learning experience? Why were they effective?

|- The activity on DNS and DHCP setup stood out for me. It combined technical knowledge with real-world application, requiring precise configurations and testing. This project was effective because it not only improved my troubleshooting skills but also reinforced my understanding of networking concepts critical for system administration.|
| :- |

Did you encounter any challenges or difficulties during the course? How did you overcome these obstacles, and what did you learn from them?

|- One challenge I faced was managing multiple configuration files in dnsmasq while ensuring all settings worked seamlessly. I overcame this by cross-referencing documentation, asking for guidance from my instructor, and conducting repeated tests to verify configurations. This taught me patience and the importance of systematic problem-solving.|
| :- |

Did the course encourage critical thinking and analysis? How did it promote higher-order thinking skills, such as problem-solving or decision-making?

|- Yes, the course encouraged critical thinking by presenting real-world problems that required thoughtful solutions. For example, while implementing multi-factor authentication into an SOP, I had to analyze potential vulnerabilities and ensure practical usability, which strengthened my decision-making and analytical skills.|
| :- |

Reflecting on your personal growth, what new knowledge, skills, or perspectives did you gain from this course?

|- I gained technical skills in configuring DNS and DHCP, monitoring web servers, and writing detailed security policies. Additionally, I developed a deeper appreciation for the role of robust authentication and system monitoring in maintaining organizational security and efficiency.|
| :- |

How do you plan to apply what you have learned in this course to your future studies, career, or personal life?

|- I plan to use these skills in future academic projects and internships, particularly in system and network management roles. The knowledge I’ve gained will be invaluable for troubleshooting, setting up secure systems, and collaborating effectively with teams in my future IT career.|
| :- |
